President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key positions within the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. The appointees include Joseph D. Gutman, who is the Managing Director of Grosvenor Capital Management and has held leadership roles with various Jewish organizations; Roman Kent, President of Namor International Corporation and a Holocaust survivor; Howard D. Unger, founder of Saw Mill Capital and son of a Holocaust survivor; Clemantine Wamariya, a survivor of the Rwandan genocide and currently an undergraduate at Yale University; and Elie Wiesel, University Professor and Holocaust survivor who has authored numerous books and played a significant role in the development of the United States Holocaust Memorial Museum. President Obama expressed confidence in these individuals' experience and dedication to their roles.